<HEADLINE>
FT  21 SEP 93 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Landed a good demand prevailed, reports the Tea Brokers' Association.
Coloury medium and selected best liquoring North Indians were firm but
plainer sorts eased, particularly pd,S. Medium East Africans were a strong
feature while brighter types opened irregularly lower but closed about
steady. Dust grades were, however, easier throughout. Ceylons sold readily
at last rates. Offshore improved competition, tending dearer. Quotations:
quality 200p/kg nom, good medium 125p/kg, medium 113p/kg, low medium 93p/kg
and nom the highest price realised this week was 253p/kg for an assam pf.
