FT  21 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Edinburgh Fund doubled to Pounds 3.72m
midway
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN, Personal Finance Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
EDINBURGH Fund Managers produced a 20 per cent increase in its interim
dividend yesterday, after a first half in which pre-tax profits more than
doubled from Pounds 1.64m to Pounds 3.72m.
Fund management income was Pounds 7.17m (Pounds 4.47m) and net profit from
unit trust trading came to Pounds 667,000 (Pounds 168,000).
After administrative expenses of Pounds 4.66m (Pounds 3.31m), operating
profits were Pounds 3.18m (Pounds 1.32m).
Earnings per share under FRS 3 were 13.8p, against 5.6p - earnings were
originally stated at 6.9p.
The interim dividend is being increased from 5p to 6p.
Funds under management increased from Pounds 2.4bn to Pounds 3bn between
January 31 and July 31, with more than half the increase representing new
business.
EFM acquired Target Trust Managers during the period, and one of its
investment trusts, EFM Dragon, took over the Drayton Asia Trust.
Investment trusts make up 42 per cent of the group's funds under management,
with an equal proportion coming from discretionary funds. The remaining 16
per cent is made up of unit trusts.
The company said 'the outlook for the full year looks satisfactory if the
present stock market levels are maintained.'
