<TEXT>
A SUBSTANTIAL cut in interest charges from Pounds 6.24m to Pounds 2.88m
helped Asda Property Holdings to raise pre-tax profits by 61 per cent to
Pounds 2.47m in the first half of 1993, against Pounds 1.53m last time.
Earnings per share more than doubled to 2.6p (1.1p), while the interim
dividend has been stepped up from 0.65p to 0.7p on capital increased by
