<HEADLINE>
FT  21 SEP 93 / Observer: Symmetry
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Nice to see Britain's armed forces boosting their clientele bases. For,
having honed their own expertise in shedding personnel over the past two
years, they are now being retained to help the Russians deal with the
effects of doing the very same.
Under an agreement signed yesterday in Moscow by defence secretary Malcolm
Rifkind, Russians will receive lessons in how to set up redundant officers
happily in Civvy Street.
So, after many years teaching citizens of developing countries how to fight
communism, Britain will now be training post-Soviet Russians how to be
civilians.
</TEXT>
