</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD DONKIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A COMMUNIST recruited by the Russians 20 years ago passed on British weapons
secrets to the KGB, it was alleged at the Old Bailey yesterday, Richard
Donkin writes.
Mr Michael Smith, an electronics graduate and an official of the Young
Communist League, spied for the KGB while working for the electronic giant
GEC, Sir Derek Spencer QC, the solicitor-general, said.
Mr Smith has denied four charges under the Official Secrets Act. He was
employed as a quality systems audit manager at the GEC Hurst research centre
then at Wembley, north-west London.
The trial continues today.
