<HEADLINE>
FT  20 SEP 93 / International Company News: Time Warner announces shake-up
in publishing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TIME WARNER, the US media group, last night announced a management shake-up
of its publishing arm, Time Inc, which it said was meant to produce
continued growth for the rest of the decade and initiative a process of
change that would virtually 'reinvent the company'.
The shake-up centres on Time Inc's New York magazine publishing operations
and, in particular, its three leading titles - Time, People and Sports
Illustrated.
At Time and People a new position, president, is being created above that of
publisher. The publisher, who previously handled a wide range of tasks, will
now focus on advertising sales. At Sports Illustrated, the previously
combined job of president and publisher is being split in two.
This is supposed to be the start of a decentralising, cost-saving process
which will involve some staff cuts, primarily through attrition. The company
is also setting up a new group to handle multi-media, which it wants to grow
into a third business leg, alongside magazines and books.
</TEXT>
